# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OAuth provider credentials (Google + GitHub)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ALL FOUR keys below are OPTIONAL. Leave them empty and the app boots normally
# with OAuth disabled — no ValueError is raised for a missing key. Populate them
# only when you want to enable "Sign in with Google" / "Sign in with GitHub".
#
# Register a SEPARATE OAuth client per environment (local / dev / prod) so a
# leaked credential in one environment can never authorize a callback in another.
#
# Callback URLs are generated by the app via url_for(<callback>, _external=True)
# (the public scheme + host come from the ProxyFix middleware) — there is no
# callback-URL env var to set. Register the resulting URL on each provider's
# console. Local callback URLs to register:
#   Google: http://127.0.0.1:8659/oauth/google/callback
#   GitHub: http://127.0.0.1:8659/oauth/github/callback
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=
GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=
